title: Bike Line XC at Fair Hill
Tour of Washington County Kick-off Criterium
2012 Tour of Washington County Stage Race
Spin 90 Cycling Basic Training
description:
Group 1:
This session will focus on interval training to increase anaerobic threshold, and how to manage and sustain your effort for a winning time.  We will polish your riding form, and make you race ready.  
Must be able to sustain a 15-20 mph average speed.

Group 2:
This session will focus on base cardio training, hill climbing techniques, when to shift, and other bike basics to help you prepare for your next event.  This course is perfect for new riders or if you just need assistance with bike skills and fitness.
Learn to ride smart and train effectively for your upcoming ride/tri.  Group sizes are small for better instructor interaction and space is limited so register today.
course:
Tuesdays class meets in Elkriged MD and offers a rolling route perfect for flat and hill intervals.
Thursdays class meets in Columbia MD and training is done on the Columbia Triathlon course and the Iron Girl/Celebration course.
registration: For questions or to register contact John Hughes at jhughes@spin90.com or visit www.tricolumbia.org

title: Juniors Day Out/ Special Olympics Maryland Regiona
St. Michaels Historic Century
description: Join special guest Bob Roll (Tour de France cyclist/commentator) and be a part of the Bike Doctor Tradition! Bicycle with friends or individually to the most scenic places surrounding historic Talbot County.
course: We are offering three routes to accommodate everyone’s needs - 25, 62.5, and 100 miles. Our flat country roads are great for training and sightseeing.
registration: Check in and late Registration for the ride begins at 7:00 a.m. Start time is at 8:00 a.m., and riders are discouraged to leave prior to this time. Riders can pick up their registration packets at the St. Michaels Elementary School. T-Shirts will be given to Pre-Registered Riders ONLY. Day of registration will be available for $50/rider.
notes: We proudly support Team4Mil and the Wounded Warrior Project\'s Adaptive Cycling Program for a second year. Join members of the 2012 RAAM team and Wounded Warrior cyclists for this memorable event! All routes begin and end in St. Michael’s. The rest stops are strategically placed to allow riders to relax and see expansive views to the water. The full Century route has a 20-minute ferry ride across the Tred Avon River to Oxford. There will be support staff at St. Michael’s Elementary School and staffed aid stations along the route.
directions:
St. Michaels Elementary School
100 Seymour Ave St. Michaels, MD

title: Hyattsville CX Little Belgians & Special Olympians
AACX - Race 4 in the Sportif Cross Cup Series
Schooley Mill Cross
description:
Hosted by Team BBC and Baltimore Bicycle Works. Race #7 in the 2011 BikeReg.com MABRAcross Super 8 Series Sunday, November 11, 2012
Held under USA Cycling Permit 2012-3492
course: With obstacles unlike any others found in the Mid-Atlantic, this is a horse of a course. This equestrian facility offers impeccable spectating as riders race across a large and varied course. The course includes several dismounts, a runup, a water hazard, a 250-meter start, and UCI-spec pits. Preride opens at 8am. Warming up on the course during races is not permitted. All USAC rules apply.
registration: Pre-register online at BikeReg.com, subject to processing fees. Online registration opens on Monday, September 25 at 8:00 pm and closes on Friday, November 9 at 12:00 noon. Onsite registration and sign-in opens at 7:00 am and closes 30 minutes prior to each race. Day-of registration is subject to $10 late fee. All riders who fail to sign in on time forfeit their spot with no refund. Riders without a USAC annual license must purchase a $10 One-Day License to race and may only compete in Cat 4 eligible events. Fields limited to 125 total riders on course; kids’ races limited to 100 total entries. Races held rain, snow, or shine. No mail-in registration. No refunds.
notes:
USAC Rules: All USAC cyclocross rules apply. Racing age is your age on December 31, 2013. All Super 8 classes will be scored separately.
Mountainbikes are permitted, but bar ends are not.
MABRAcross Super 8 Series Rules: For complete series rules and scored classes, visit
http://www.mabracross.org/rulebook/
Staging: Assigned start positions are for pre-registered riders only and will be ordered by bib number.
Staging will be based on current Super 8 series standings followed by order of registration and
promoter discretion.
Prizes: Elite Men payout: $900 over 10 places ($150, $135, $120, $105, $90, $80, $70, $60, $50, $40).
Elite Women: $600 over 7 places ($150, $125, $100, $75, $60, $50, $40).
All other adults: merchandise
Juniors: medals five places deep.
Kids race: medals for all.
directions: From I-95 take exit 35B to MD 216/Scaggsville Road West. Pass through four round-abouts. Turn left on Hall Shop Road, left into the park.
